reviews.text:
About the train station: They have just two platforms, very easy! Also public toilets, an information center and a service to take/leave books!

About the village: it is amazing!

Very bad service every time I go to buy a ticket the ticket office is closed. I can’t use the ticket
Machine as it is bright sunlight all day and you can’t see the instructions etc. And being a pensioner it is very frustrating. The ticket office is closed for at least 3 hours a day. Most of the staff are very friendly and helpful but there is one gentleman who is most unhelpful on all occasions I’ve been served him the experience is not very good sorry to say. I have been down to the station 5 times in the last 2 days to purchase a ticket but 3 times not open then payment machine not working now I’ve been told the computer isn’t working. Very unhelpful and frustrating to say the least it looks like I will have to board my train with
No ticket and get it from the ticket inspector on the train. Phoned national rail no knowledge of problem at the station and I ask myself why in this day and age it is 2019 not 1919!
One of the nice town in Kent. Lovely high street with unique shops ! Don't forget to grab a fish and chips and enjoy at the beach!
Nice and clean trains and service!
This is a really nice place to come to. People are very friendly and kind. The town is clean. The sea is beautiful. I highly recommend coming here.
